                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <locus from="79r" to="121r"/>
                     <title ref="LIT7679MarhaEwur"/>
                     
                     <note>The text is divided into two parts,
                         each beginning with dates. The dates do not much exactly. 1) <locus target="#79ra"/>: <date calendar="creation" when="7569" when-custom="2076" evidence="internal"> 7569 ʿamata śǝggāwe ‘year of the
                           Incarnation’</date> (most likely the scribe meant the year of Incarnation <date calendar="ethiopian"  when ="1569" when-custom="2076" evidence="internal">1569, i.e., 1576 A.D.</date>), and 
                           <date calendar="diocletian" when="1299" when-custom="1583" evidence="internal"> 1299 ʿamata samāʿtāt ‘year of the martyrs’ (= 1583 A.D)</date>.
                          2) <locus target="#106vb"/>: <date calendar="creation" when="7202" when-custom="1702" evidence="internal"> 7202 ʿamata ʿālam ‘year of the
                        world’ (= 1702 A.D.)</date>, <date calendar="ethiopian" when="1702" when-custom="1709" evidence="internal">1702 ʿamata śǝggāwe (= 1709 A.D.)</date> and 
                        <date calendar="diocletian" when="1427" when-custom="1711" evidence="internal">1427 ʿamata samāʿtāt (= 1711 A.D.)</date>.  The time span indicated by these dates is about 136 years. 
                       Some sections include records of historical events from ca. 1570 to 1702, e.g.,  on <locus target="#80ra"/>
                        on the death of Yǝsḥaq, 
                        <locus target="#81ra"/> on killing of ‘ʾAboli Gāllā’, 
                        <locus target="#82ra"/> on campaign to Kʷārā, on the coming of Žān Medā, 
                        <locus target="#83ra"/> on the death of Queen <persName ref="PRS1429AdmasMo"/>, 
                        <locus target="#83vb"/> on the enthronement of ḥaḍe <persName ref="PRS10194Yaeqob"/>, 
                        <locus target="#84vb"/> on the argument between ḥaḍe <persName ref="PRS10198Yaeqob"/> and Rās <persName ref="PRS2226Atnatewo"/>, 
                        <locus target="#85rb"/> on the death of ḥaḍe <persName ref="PRS10513Zadenge"/>, 
                        <locus target="#86ra"/> on the victory of ḥaḍe <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> over Wǝr(ǝ)nšo (Oromo), 
                        <locus target="#92va"/> on the death of <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> and the enthronement of <persName ref="PRS4015Fasilada"/>. 
                        Some other historical records, in smaller script, by the same and various hand(s) are inserted beside and below the
                        main text on <locus target="#79va #82vb #95va #96rab"/>.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  
