                        <item xml:id="a11">
                           <locus target="#95vb"/>
                           <desc>Note on the arrival of two unnamed metropolitans to Ethiopia. It is carefully written in a neat hand.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">በዝንቱ፡ ዘመን፡ መጽኡ፡ ፪፡ ጳጳሳት፡ ፩፡ በደንካሌ፡ ወ፩፡ በስናር፡ ዘመጽአ፡ በስናር፡ ተሰይመ</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en">In this year came two metropolitans, one by Dankāle and one by Sǝnnār. The one who came by Sǝnnār was appointed.</q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a12">
                           <locus from="120v" to="121ra"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText"><title ref ="LIT4145Onausp"/>; it is written in a mediocre hand.</desc>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a13">
                           <locus target="#121rab"/>, <locus target="#121va"/>
                           <desc type="GuestText">Protective prayers against abdominal pains, snake bites
                              and the evil eye. </desc>
                           <note>Crudely written, in the same hand as additions <ref target="#a4 #a5 #a6 #a7 #a15"/>.</note>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ሕማመ፡ ከርሥ፡ አንተ፡ አምላከ፡ አብርሃም፡ </q>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a14">
